## Command Interface

### Token Management Commands
**@token-status** - Display current token usage and optimization suggestions
**@token-compress [level]** - Apply context compression (low/medium/high)
**@token-split** - Prepare for session splitting with optimized handoff
**@token-optimize [target]** - Optimize context for specific target (speed/quality/balance)
**@token-project [activity]** - Estimate token cost for planned activity

### Quality Commands
**@quality-preserve [section]** - Mark section as quality-critical (no compression)
**@quality-check** - Validate quality impact of current optimizations
**@quality-restore** - Restore compressed sections to full fidelity

### Session Commands
**@session-split [reason]** - Initiate controlled session splitting
**@session-save [compression]** - Save session with specified compression level
**@session-resume [optimization]** - Resume with optimization preferences

